Subject: failure to uninstall agent version 6.2.1.2004 on windows 11 device
Description: When the client tries to uninstall the agent in one of the devices he has, at first, he gets an error of a missing dll package wich is "MSIInstallerDLL.dll" file. When the client replaces the dll file with another dll file from another device with the same agent, it all works but the agent wizard appears to him asking for a password they don't have configured on the server.
What_We_Know__c: The customer could not uninstall the EPP Client from one of the machines
Next_Steps__c:
During a remote session we used the ZAP tool in order to remove the EPP Client.
Waiting for the customer to confirm if the ticket can be closed.
Solution_Comment__c:
Customer forgot the uninstall password assigned to an old machine which was not communicating with the EPP Server.
We removed the client with the zap tool
